# Overview

This report examines participant-level correlations across the main outcome families. The goal is not to test the experimental conditions again. Instead, the goal is to ask whether different outcomes appear to measure the same kind of learning, or whether they capture different aspects of participants' understanding.

The main outcomes are organized so that higher values are easier to interpret as **better performance or stronger interest**. For value estimation, the original score is an error score, so I reverse its direction by multiplying mean absolute error by -1. In other words, higher value-estimation performance means **lower estimation error**.

