# 3. Correlation matrix

I use Spearman correlations as the main correlation metric because several outcomes are bounded, discrete, or based on only a few items. Spearman correlations ask whether participants who score higher on one outcome also tend to score higher on another, without assuming a perfectly linear relationship.

```{r correlations}
cor_pairwise <- calc_pairwise_cor(outcome_family, main_correlation_vars, method = "spearman") |>
  mutate(
